text: The Division of Clark (named Denison until 2018) is one of the five multi- member electorates in the Tasmanian House of Assembly. It is named after Andrew Inglis Clark. Clark includes most of the city of Hobart, including the inner-city parts of the city. It shares the same boundaries as the federal Division of Clark, which only has one member. ==Election results== ==References== Clark
